# ChangeLog

All notable changes to this project are documented in this file.

## Unreleased

Date: 2026-06-02

### Changed (2026-07-19 licensing links)

- Added original-language license links to the licensing sections on index.html, ethics.html, and coc.html for the GNU Free Documentation License, GNU Affero General Public License, and CC BY-SA.
- Added a Public Domain link entry in the licensing sections so the QB Networks logo source is clearly labeled across all public pages.

### Files (2026-07-19 licensing links)

- ChangeLog
- README.md
- README.tr.md
- index.html
- ethics.html
- coc.html

### Changed (2026-07-19 references, navigation, licensing)

- Added bidirectional reference navigation in ethics.html so each principle quote marker `[1]..[10]` opens the matching reference entry and each reference includes a return link.
- Updated reference wording in ethics.html to match the profile README style and wording, including "Back to reference N" phrasing.
- Retargeted return links to full principle cards so users land on the entire principle block (title, paragraph, and quote), improving readability.
- Added principle-card anchor IDs and reference IDs for stable in-page linking.
- Improved in-page anchor visibility by adding `scroll-margin-top` and `:target` highlighting for principle cards and references.
- Reduced header height and navigation footprint (logo size, spacing, and link sizing) so more principle content is visible after anchor jumps.
- Updated artwork licensing notes to specify that the QB Networks logo is Public Domain with source link: https://openclipart.org/detail/62191/semantic-social-network.
- Applied the logo Public Domain licensing note consistently in ethics.html and coc.html.

### Files (2026-07-19 references, navigation, licensing)

- ChangeLog
- README.md
- README.tr.md
- ethics.html
- coc.html
- styles.css

### Changed (2026-07-19 release script token/tag flow)

- Updated scripts/publish-release.sh so it can run without explicit `--tag` by selecting the latest git tag automatically.
- Added positional tag support (`./publish-release.sh v20260719`) in addition to the `--tag` option.
- Added direct token options `--github-token` and `--codeberg-token` for non-interactive automation.
- Kept environment and git-config token sources and introduced hidden terminal prompt fallback (`read -s`) when tokens are not provided.
- Improved usage/help text to document token lookup order and no-argument behavior.

### Files (2026-07-19 release script token/tag flow)

- ChangeLog
- README.md
- README.tr.md
- scripts/publish-release.sh

### Changed

- Reworked the landing page content around the Free Software Free Society message and removed the old stats, live preview, focus areas, CTA buttons, and email list sections.
- Updated project branding from "QB Networks Web Development Team" to "QB Networks" across the site and documentation.
- Switched the visible site branding and favicon to img/qbnetworks400x400.svg and removed the old colored background from the SVG artwork.
- Added ethics.html and coc.html as first-class themed pages sharing the same design system as the home page.
- Unified the main navigation across pages with Home, Ethics, and Code of Conduct links.
- Added LibreJS-friendly footer text on all public pages with direct JavaScript source, website source code, AGPLv3-or-later license, and copyright links.
- Simplified front-end behavior in script.js to keep only shared header, menu, and reveal logic after removing stats and form handling.
- Updated English and Turkish README files to reflect the current site structure, branding, and licensing details.

### Changed (2026-06-03)

- Reworked the header layout on all public pages to a centered, stacked structure: brand (logo + QB Networks) at the top and navigation links centered directly underneath.
- Removed the temporary logo-only and extra centered-logo block variants after iterative UI adjustments, keeping a consistent brand block in the header.
- Standardized brand behavior so the top QB Networks brand link on the home page now points to index.html instead of index.html#top.
- Center-aligned the home hero content so the "Free Software Free Society" heading and its supporting paragraph are visually centered.
- Reduced the hero title size for better balance with the centered layout.
- Switched site typography to a monospace stack across pages.
- Added a shared bottom "Source Code" + "Additional Links" section to index.html and coc.html to match ethics.html.
- Removed duplicate Source Code card content from coc.html so all pages use the same bottom links pattern.

